# Manu Works

Personal website of **Emanuel F.**, created to present my work, projects, and presence as a developer.

## About

**Manu Works** is my personal portfolio.
It brings together information about me, my projects, and the way I build digital solutions.

This project is a clone of another project of mine called [Mythos](https://github.com/charliepeanut/mythos), which works as a base for creating websites. From that structure, I adapted the content, identity, and pages to build this personal website.

The project was developed with a simple, organized, and easy-to-maintain structure in mind.

## Technologies

This project uses **Webpack** to compile and organize the final website files.

Main features:

* templates with **Nunjucks**;
* styles with **SCSS**;
* scripts in **JavaScript**;
* static asset copying and processing;
* automatic HTML page generation.

## Technical structure

Webpack automatically loads scripts and styles from the assets folders, processes `.njk` templates, and generates the final HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files.

Pages are created from templates located in:

```txt id="xuoep5"
src/pages/
```

The final files are organized into:

```txt id="qy4as8"
assets/
├── media/
├── scripts/
└── styles/
```

## Build

During the build process, the project:

* compiles SCSS styles;
* generates HTML files;
* bundles JavaScript scripts;
* copies static assets to the final output folder.

